snippet.textDisplay: Last semester I had to do a presentation on cluster B personality disorders (Borderline, histrionic, antisocial, narcissistic) for my english class. After I finished the main presentation, my professor asked “how do you feel about multiple personality disorder?” I had to explain to her that DID had absolutely nothing to do with personality disorders; I found her ignorance concerning and a bit insulting. I hope more people watch your videos so that eventually I will no longer have to deal with this ignorance.

snippet.textDisplay: I have learned so much from your videos thank you for all the hard work you put in them!! One video idea I had was for you to show different fashion preferences for some of your alters, and how you collectively choose makeup or outfits for the day! I think it's so funny how skilled Nin is with makeup but I remember watching a video where Kyle struggled even know which brushes were which. Do some of your more bold makeup looks intimidate the littles? What happens if a non-human alter fronts and decides to change your look for the day? It may seem like a less pressing topic but it would be a more lighthearted discussion if you are struggling that day. If you don't want to answer some of those questions I still would love to see your fashion choices as individual alters! I love your system so much and can't wait to watch more of your videos! <3

snippet.textDisplay: I don't know if you'll see this since there are SO MANY comments, but have you considered a video about confused switches? For example, not knowing who you are... co-fronting... confusion while co-conscious... Getting traits from co-con alters (like with bubbliness or accents that are not your own)... etc. Like sometimes I will have an accent with Marcus is around because he has an accent. Sometimes we don't know who we are when we first wake up or when we're stressed... -Axel

snippet.textDisplay: We try to have as much fun with our DID as we can. It's not because we think it's cool, exciting or fun. It sucks. PTSD HURTS! But it's the lot we were given. We have to make the best of it. As our gatekeeper always says, "Laugh. Because if you don't laugh, you'll cry." We choose to laugh whenever we can. - Axel
